<p class="k2-news-post__prose">
	Big news from Italy today: Active Soccer 3, the arcade football game created by our very own Gianluca Troiano, officially launches on <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2187300/Active_Soccer_3/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Steam</a> today, July 13, 2026, leaving early access as the full 1.0 release. The game is developed and published by Gianluca&rsquo;s own studio, <a href="https://www.thefoxsoftware.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Fox Software</a>.
</p>
<p class="k2-news-post__prose">
	To Kick Off 2 players, Gianluca needs no introduction. He is a three-time Kick Off 2 World Champion, and not just any three: he took gold at <a href="/amiga/tournament/event-stats.php?id=115#tournament">Groningen 2003</a>, <a href="/amiga/tournament/event-stats.php?id=140#tournament">Milan 2004</a> and <a href="/amiga/tournament/event-stats.php?id=169#tournament">Cologne 2005</a>, three World Cups in a row, adding a silver and two bronze medals along the way. Few people on this planet understand fast arcade football the way Gianluca does, and for many years he has been pouring exactly that understanding into the Active Soccer series.
</p>
<figure class="k2-news-post__figure">
	<img src="/images/amiga/news/as3-launch-action.jpg" width="1200" height="675" alt="Active Soccer 3 screenshot: top-down arcade football match in a packed stadium, attacking players closing in on the goal." loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
	<figcaption>Active Soccer 3: fast-paced arcade football in front of a packed house. Image: The Fox Software.</figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="k2-news-post__prose">
	Active Soccer 3 carries the spirit of the 16-bit era classics into the modern age: fast-paced, easy to learn and hard to master, playable with up to 4 players on the same screen. Beyond the arcade action there is a full career mode with more than 30 leagues and over 1,000 clubs, a transfer market, a competition designer for building your own tournaments, and matches in all kinds of weather, day and night. And as a special treat for Amiga hearts: the soundtrack is by none other than Chris H&uuml;lsbeck (Turrican, anyone?). You can get a taste of both the action and the music in the launch trailer below.
</p>
